|WKO=====================================================================
|YKOBanks keep your coins safe and power the bidding economy. All branches
share a single account, opened automatically the first time you walk
into a bank. The commands above only work inside a bank.

  |YKBdeposit <amount>|YKO   Move coins from your pockets into the bank.
  |YKBwithdraw <amount>|YKO  Take coins back out.
  |YKBbalance|YKO            Show balance, liens, and amount available.
  |YKBtransfer <amount> from <alt>|YKO
                     Pull coins from one of your own registered alts'
                     accounts into this character's account.
  |YKBlien|YKO               Show any lien held against your account.

Use "all" in place of an amount to move everything at once. Ghosts
cannot bank; get resurrected first.

Liens: part of your balance can be held in escrow for a pending deal,
most commonly an outstanding auction bid or a pub purchase. Liened
coins stay yours but cannot be withdrawn until the deal completes or
falls through. |YKBbalance|YKO always shows how much is free and clear.

The bank pays no interest -- it offers safekeeping, not growth. Coins
must be on deposit to back auction bids, so keep your bidding money
banked (see |CKBhelp auction|YKO).

Branches operate in most large settlements, including the Bank of
DarkWind in DarkWind City, the Souvrael Money Handlers in Souvrael,
and the Grimsfjord Banking House in Hyperborea. Any branch reaches
the same account.|XX0

